XI. 11. cohortem praetoriam: since the time of the younger Scipio, a body-guard attending the general. It was composed partly of veterans who voluntarily offered their services for that purpose (evocati), partly of young nobles, who in this way gained experience in the art of war.

15. eiectam: stranded.
